OL,6,FHowever, overall, there was a 5%
OL,7,Fdecrease in hate crime offences across
OL,8,Fthe board, including for race, sexual
OL,9,Forientation disability and transgender
OL,10,Frelated hate crimes.
OL,12,FReligious hate crimes targeted at
OL,13,FJewish people more than doubled over
OL,14,Fthe course of a year to 3,282
OL,15,Fincidents, accounting for a third
OL,16,F(33%) of all religious hate crimes,
OL,17,Fcompared to 20% in 2023.
